name: Franz Schubert
biography: Franz Schubert was an Austrian composer of the late Classical and early Romantic eras. Despite his short life, Schubert was incredibly prolific, composing over six hundred vocal works, as well as symphonies, operas, and a large body of chamber and piano music. His music is notable for its emotional depth, memorable melodies, and rich harmonies.
